Hi again,

On Tue, May 28, 2002 at 04:27:27AM +1000, John Max Skaller wrote:

> If so.. how about some language for generating
> Ocaml/C binding code? Surely that would make
> handling things easier than the existing macro solution?

Camlp4 cannot do that, because it only treats programs having the
semantics of OCaml to be treated later by the OCaml compiler. The
interface OCaml/C does not have the semantics of OCaml: it is just C
program.

